8.2 Process

1. authenticate,


2. validate scopes,


3. validate jurisdiction,


4. validate balance,


5. derive HD path,


6. canonicalize,


7. hash,


8. sign,


9. persist,


10. emit outbox,


11. update snapshots.




---

9. Ledger state

9.1 States

open

posting

posted

reconciling

reconciled

adjustment_required

adjusted

locked

closed

archived


9.2 Rule

Closed periods cannot be modified. Only compensating entries are allowed.


---

10. Persistent idempotency

10.1 Key

tenantId + orgId + ledgerId + reference + operationType + idempotencyKey

10.2 Result

Repeated requests:

do not duplicate entries,

do not affect balances,

return the same result.



---

11. Cryptographic signing

11.1 Algorithm

Ed25519

HSM/KMS custody


11.2 Scope

canonical payload only.


11.3 Purpose

integrity,

authenticity,

non-repudiation,

distributed trust.



---

12. Outbox / Inbox / DLQ

12.1 Outbox

Events are stored alongside the transaction.

12.2 Inbox

Consumers track processed events.

12.3 DLQ

Irrecoverable events are stored with failure reasons.


